  "text": "The incidence of oral cancer is 12.5/100,000 and the largest numbers of oral cancer patients are present in India [CITATION_1] . In India, oral cancer includes 9.4 percent of all cancers [CITATION_2] . This epidemic proportion of oral cancer in India is due to the rampant use of betel nut, betel quid, and gutkha and pan masala chewing which are proven to be carcinogens [CITATION_3] . Oral cancer is uncommon disease in the West but continue to be the major cause of cancer related death in Indian men [CITATION_4] . Over last few decades, large funds have been spent to educate public, implement laws effectively, rehabilitate tobacco growers, build cessation facility, create health care infrastructure, etc to reduce the betel nut, betel quid, ",
